<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="All-hail1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">All-hail,</orth> subst. a term of salutation, expressing a wish of health and happiness: <cit><quote>give the a. to thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 3, 139</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>greater than both, by the a. hereafter,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.5.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 5, 56</bibl></cit>. Without the hyphen: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.189" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 189</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 158</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.169" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 169</bibl> etc. cf. <emph>Hail.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>